This paper deals with the concept of algorithmic randomness, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The paper also discusses the use of bounded Kolmogorov-Loveland selection rules, which are commonly used in algorithmic information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
